dcterms:description: The IEEE-30 Bus System is a standard test case used for power flow analysis, consisting of 30 buses, 6 generators, 41 branches, 4 transformers, and 21 fixed loads. It is utilized to study and minimize power losses in distribution networks.
dcterms:title: IEEE-30 Bus System

dcterms:creator: C. Lei
dcterms:description: The IEEE-30 Bus Data provides detailed information about the bus system, including voltage magnitudes, transformer data, and shunt capacitor data, which are essential for conducting power flow analysis.
dcterms:title: IEEE-30 Bus Data
